spans.text: to sigh one last adieu , Nor scorn a sorrow friendship owes to you : A friendship modesty might well return
how the miser , pierced with inward pain
chides the waves that rolled Himself ashore
Pain too has lavished all her killing store
Pain too has lavished all her killing store
Courage to conquer evils , or endure : Sweetness to sooth the pain , and smiles
not to credit all she sees or hears
the evil only in her fears
the evil only in her fears
to weigh the fact in even scale
To ask the pity fame will never approve
that it slumbers , and expects , in vain , To see the little cherub live again
the shade and substance were the same
